title: Pictured Rocks National Lakeshore: Cooperating Association
body: Explore This Park    Get Involved     Support Your Park     Cooperating Association              Cooperating Association            Eastern National is a non-profit organization that provides quality educational products and services to America’s national parks and other public trusts.   Eastern National (EN) functions as a part of the interpretive arm of the National Park Service, a business that acquires or produces and sells materials to enhance the enjoyment of park visitors, and a philanthropic organization that disperses its net income to the NPS for its diverse interpretive and educational programs.   Eastern National operates bookstores at three visitor centers at Pictured Rocks National Lakeshore and also conducts sales by phone, mail, and website, "America's National Park On-line Bookstore."   All purchases benefit Pictured Rocks National Lakeshore. The Superior Wildlands interagency annual newspaper receives major funding through the generosity of Eastern National. EN also provides support for special park events.      Serving the Visitors to America's National Parks and Other Public Trusts  Eastern National  470 Maryland Drive Suite 1 Ft.
